{
  "texts": [
    "Bothe et all [12] used curriculum learning to order training samples, but their work uses the full dataset for training.",
    "Meanwhile, AI in telecommunications has expanded rapidly, powering applications from network traffic forecasting [13] to load balancing, radio access network (RAN) tuning, and fault prediction.",
    "Yet, model training is often treated as a black box, with little examination of how training data characteristics affect reliability, retraining frequency, or energy use.",
    "As networks shift toward dynamic architectures like Open-RAN and edge-cloud splits, models must adapt to continuously evolving data streams by making efficient retraining not just beneficial, but necessary.",
    "Environmental costs are also rising."
  ]
}